:"Datingscout"},"description":"Famous for its geothermal features including bubbling mud pools, hot springs, and geysers, Rotorua offers a unique natural spectacle combined with Maori cultural experiences. The city is essential for experiencing New Zealand's volcanic landscape and indigenous heritage."},{"rank":4,"name":"Queenstown","placeId":"queenstown","regionId":"southland","regionName":"Southland","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1692098601789-478d2a0c03b9?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxRdWVlbnN0b3duJTIwTGFrZSUyMFdha2F0aXB1JTIwbW91bnRhaW5zfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM5MjcxMzd8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Gabriel Van Duinen"},"description":"An adventure capital nestled on Lake Wakatipu, offering world-class activities from bungee jumping and skiing to hiking and jet boating. The town combines outdoor thrills with excellent restaurants, bars, and stunning mountain scenery."},{"rank":5,"name":"Tongariro National Park","placeId":"tongariro_national_park","regionId":"manawatu_wanganui","regionName":"Manawatū-Whanganui","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1585050820294-08a3ed204927?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUb25nYXJpcm8lMjBBbHBpbmUlMjBDcm9zc2luZ3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzODk0OTY1fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Adrien Aletti"},"description":"Home to the world-famous Tongariro Alpine Crossing, this UNESCO World Heritage park features three active volcanic mountains with otherworldly landscapes. The region offers exceptional hiking, geothermal wonders, and stunning alpine scenery."},{"rank":6,"name":"Wellington","placeId":"wellington_city","regionId":"wellington","regionName":"Wellington","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589871973318-9ca1258faa5d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxXZWxsaW5ndG9uJTIwTmV3JTIwWmVhbGFuZHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzg0MDM0NTg4fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Sulthan Auliya"},"description":"New Zealand's capital city is a vibrant cultural center known for its creative scene, museums, harbor views, and film industry heritage. It serves as both a major tourist destination and the country's political and cultural heart."},{"rank":7,"name":"Bay of Islands","placeId":"bay_of_islands","regionId":"northland","regionName":"Northland","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593210563043-6bec3f4bebee?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCYXklMjBvZiUyMElzbGFuZHMlMjBOZXclMjBaZWFsYW5kJTIwYWVyaWFsfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM4ODczMDV8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Linde Lanjouw"},"description":"A stunning coastal area featuring 144 islands, pristine beaches, and crystalline waters that rank among New Zealand's most picturesque seascapes. It's perfect for sailing, dolphin watching, fishing, and exploring secluded bays by boat."},{"rank":8,"name":"Franz Josef Glacier","placeId":"franz_josef_glacier","regionId":"west_coast","regionName":"West Coast","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1548070598-3f6d85abb218?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxGcmFueiUyMEpvc2VmJTIwR2xhY2llciUyMG1vdW50YWlufGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM4OTU3Mjl8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Matt Palmer"},"description":"A massive and accessible glacier in the Southern Alps that descends into temperate rainforest, making it a unique geological wonder. It's one of New Zealand's most iconic natural attractions and offers hiking, helicopter tours, and glacier walks."},{"rank":9,"name":"Fiordland National Park","placeId":"fiordland_national_park","regionId":"fiordland","regionName":"Fiordland","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1475061310011-970c2da77d72?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxGaW9yZGxhbmQlMjBOYXRpb25hbCUyMFBhcmslMjBOZXclMjBaZWFsYW5kfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODQwMzQ0NDR8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Sam Ferrara"},"description":"New Zealand's largest national park encompasses stunning fjords, waterfalls, and wilderness, with Milford Sound and Doubtful Sound as flagship attractions. The remote dramatic landscape and world-class tramping tracks make it a destination for serious hikers and nature lovers."},{"rank":10,"name":"Abel Tasman National Park","placeId":"abel_tasman_national_park","regionId":"nelson_tasman","regionName":"Nelson & Tasman","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1668010884237-a469a7c93c93?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxBYmVsJTIwVGFzbWFuJTIwTmF0aW9uYWwlMjBQYXJrJTIwYmVhY2hlc3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzOTI3MjM5fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Esther Grosscurt"},"description":"This stunning coastal national park features pristine golden beaches, crystal-clear waters, and native forest accessible by hiking the famous Abel Tasman Coast Track. Visitors can kayak between beaches, swim with seals, and experience some of New Zealand's most spectacular coastal scenery."}]}